      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WAVE OF FUN (1) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors four on end. Last start collided in the run and finished third in a Grade 5/6 at Mandurah (23.04). Rates a top chance. LITTLE DITZY (4) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors five on end. Last start rocketed out of the boxes with a scorching early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when third (22.17) at this track over 381m. Deserves a win and gets her chance. TRICEP KING (2) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fifth (17.89) in a Grade 6 at Northam. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to her name from eight starts. Better than last start and can bounce back. CRENSHAW KING (5) was in the money last start here at this trip - likely to feature again.",
